title: The Realty Gateway Cup - Giro Della Montagna
Kansas City Cup Cross
description: Come join us for the 2nd annual KC Cup Cyclocross Race. This race is part of Kansas City Cup Festival weekend with a Saturday Cyclocross race and a Sunday MTB race. We invite you to make it a full Cup weekend. This is the 1st race of Series 60 Cyclocross, a local 8 race series within Kansas City Metro area (www.series60cx.com/), and the 1st CX race in the Kansas City area. We will kick off the season in grand fashion.
course: Course will involve grass, pavement, and sections of fast wide open wooded trail.
registration: Registration will open at 9:30 AM on the day of the race. Registration for each event closes 30 minutes before the posted race start time. USAC license required to ride USAC categories. One-day USAC license available for $10. Fees include $3 for USAC insurance.
notes: All USAC rules apply. Race will be held rain or shine. CPSC approved helmets must be worn by all participants while riding at any time during this event. Mountain bikes are allowed just no bar ends. Promoter reserve the right to combine categories.
directions:
From the West: From 71 HWY, head east on East Gregory Blvd. to Oldham Road (right/east). Turn right on Oldham Road. Go apx. 1 mile to Oakwood Drive entrance (Camp Lake of the Woods). Turn left. Follow the signs for parking at the top of the hill.
From the East: From I-435. Gregory Blvd exit. Head west approx. 2 miles to Oldham Road (just past Lake of the Woods.) Turn Left. Go apx. 1 mile to Oakwood Drive entrance (Camp Lake of the Woods). Turn left. Follow the signs for parking at the top of the hill.

title: Council Bluff Challenge
description: Council Bluff Challenge is a United Federation of Dirt XC race at Council Bluff lake near Potosi, Missouri.  The race is held on Mark Twain National Forest lands.
course: The race course is 12.4 miles in length and encircles the lake, up and down ravines and across the reservoir dam.  The trail base is very firm, of hardpacked gravelly soil and rocks.  There are some steep climbs and descents and a few technical rocky sections, with a couple low water creek crossing thrown in.
registration: Register on site starting at 7 AM, day of the race.  Registration closes 30 minuted before the start of each race.
directions: From Potosi, take Highway P south for 13 miles.  Turn right on Highway C, go just 1/4 mile and turn left on Highway DD.  Go about 7 miles to the entrance of the park.  Turn at the sign and follow the paved access road to the park entrance, then follow race signs to parking.
